# Backend Testing

## Framework

JUnit 5 via `spring-boot-starter-test`. Security tests use `spring-security-test` (`@WithMockUser`).

## Controller tests

MockMvc-based, one test class per controller (e.g., `OwnerRestControllerTests`):

- Use `@SpringBootTest` + `@WebAppConfiguration` + `@ContextConfiguration(classes = ApplicationTestConfig.class)`
- Build MockMvc in `@BeforeEach` with `MockMvcBuilders.standaloneSetup(controller).setControllerAdvice(new ExceptionControllerAdvice())`
- Mock the `ClinicService` with `@Mock`, inject real mappers with `@Autowired`
- Use `@WithMockUser(roles = "OWNER_ADMIN")` (or `VET_ADMIN`, `ADMIN`) for secured endpoints
- Test security is enabled in test properties: `petclinic.security.enable=true`

## Service integration tests

`AbstractClinicServiceTests` defines shared test methods. Three subclasses activate different profiles:

- `ClinicServiceJdbcTests` → `@ActiveProfiles({"jdbc", "hsqldb"})`
- `ClinicServiceJpaTests` → `@ActiveProfiles({"jpa", "hsqldb"})`
- `ClinicServiceSpringDataJpaTests` → `@ActiveProfiles({"spring-data-jpa", "hsqldb"})`

## Coverage

`jacoco-maven-plugin` enforces coverage; excludes generated `rest/dto` and `rest/api` packages. Run `./mvnw test` to execute all backend tests.
